entry.title: Cookie Policy: Disable 3PC when default content setting is block
entry.content:
When the default cookie setting is set to BLOCK, the Block 3PC

preference is meaningless - it can never impact access decisions.



For enterprise policies, we can easily surface this relationship to

users by following the standard enterprise pattern and disabling

3PC with policy indicators on affected controls.



To avoid requiring each UI surface which represents the 3PC setting

state to check multiple locations for management information, this

CL updates the policy handler to simply set the block 3PC pref

directly, so it naturally appears managed.



This does not change the semantics of any policies, but simply makes

representing the effective state to users easier.

entry.title: Prefetch: Keep prefetch queued when at the limit
entry.content:
Currently, when we've reached the limit of number of completed

prefetches and we can't evict any prefetches to make room, we destroy

the queued prefetch under consideration. This CL updates this

behaviour, and now keeps the prefetch under consideration queued, and

tries to find another prefetch.



This CL also tries to trigger a new prefetch anytime an existing

prefetch is destroyed, to deal with a scenario where a prefetch times

out and we have other prefetches queued up. This could cause a

potential rentrancy into PrefetchService::Prefetch() when we evict

while trying to consider if a prefetch can be started, so we no longer

evict in CanPrefetchNow(), but only when we're about to start the

next prefetch.

entry.title: Simplify IsMinimumAddress().
entry.content:
Currently, IsMinimumAddress() is two unnecessary parameters:

- app_locale: It's only used to construct an AutofillCountry object in

GetAutofillProfileRequirementResult(). However, the optional

app_locale parameter is only needed to translate the country name.

If AutofillCountry::name() is not used, like in the case of checking

requirements, it can be omitted.

- predicted_country_code: All callsites use the profile's country.*

This CL removes them both.



* There's some historical context why it was added in the first place,

and why it is no longer necessary. In the past, complementing the

country happened before the multi-step import logic. So during multi-

step imports (which checks address requirements too), it was necessary

to recompute the complemented country whenever something was merged.

[1] changed this behavior and swapped the order. Since then, by the

any time requirements are checked, the country is already

complemented.



[1] https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bwgKfCeDdXVMghgDdnJ0Mla-GW8DP2IbMz3mwO_ifk0/edit?resourcekey=0-jr163i3QOo9yrKW3j9yWDA#heading=h.v2wyouz52iot

entry.title: [DBSC] Check if the /RotateBoundCookies sets the required cookies
entry.content:
The cookie header is not present in the response of the cookie rotation

request that is propagated from the network to the browser process.



Unexpected server response i.e. not setting the required cookies is

considered a persistent error.



This CL adds a cookie observer to the rotation request. The observer is

called with `network::mojom::CookieAccessDetails::Type::kChange` with

cookies set in the response of the request if there are any. The cookies

are verified to contain the required cookie.



Normally, a cookie update notification should be sent before the request

is complete. We add some leeway using a timer in the case mojo messages

are delivered out of order.

entry.title: Make LayoutSVGContainer drive transform updates
entry.content:
Drop the `bounds_changed` argument passed to `CalculateLocalTransform()`

and handle the potential need for implicit transform invalidation in

LayoutSVGContainer::UpdateLayout().



Make only LayoutSVGContainer handle the `needs_transform_update_` flag,

and make the transform update itself the only responsibility of the

various subclasses.



Rename LayoutSVGContainer::CalculateLocalTransform to

UpdateLocalTransform to better reflect what it does - since it has

side-effects.



Move the transform invalidation for 'x' and 'y' on to style update

time, and only update it in the corresponding transform update hook. Add

a case to SVGContentContainer::Layout() to handle when the viewport

itself changes and 'x' and/or 'y' is a percentage.

entry.title: [PWAs-in-Play] Allow migration between multiple APK PWA packages
entry.content:
If multiple ARC packages attempt to install the same web app, they will

silently conflict and repeatedly switch which package is associated with

the app in prefs. Additionally, uninstalling the web app will take

multiple attempts to remove the app, as the duplicate PWA package will

reinstall it immediately after the app is uninstalled the first time.



For the case of apps which are migrating between Play Store listings, it

is possible that users who install both listings will end up in this

state, with both apps installed. To resolve this, we silently migrate

the user state, uninstalling the 'deprecated' package, and associating

the app with the 'canonical' package. We do not attempt to automatically

detect duplicates, but rather rely on a hardcoded list of impacted

packages.

entry.title: [File F2] Use VolumeManager.isAllowedVolume() to filter volumes
entry.content:
Context:

Previously Navigation reducer use VolumeManager's volumeInfoList to

check if a volume is allowed or not, but the addVolume action is

dispatched before the VolumeInfo is added to the VolumeInfoList, which

makes the navigation reducer skip that volume because it's not inside

the VolumeInfoList. The result is that the newly mounted volume won't show in the directory tree.



This CL exposes the isAllowedVolume() method from the VolumeManager so

Navigation reducer can use it to check if a volume is allowed or not.



Note: "directoryTreeExpandFolderOnDelayExpansionVolume" browser test

breaks with the store version directory tree without this fix.

sync status map (ensures it is not one of the 200 items in progress).

Creating swap file for renderer only depends on parkable

string feature enabled. But ParkableImagesToDisk also requires

DiskDataAllocator. So this CL makes creating swap file in

special case(ParkableImages on / CompressParkableStrings off).
